From ed3964308d2d9223ed7a41ec24e5e2eba7a57acf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: HALTER <halter.elie@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 10:29:20 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 01/13] Add prescribed displacement BC from external
 displacement file

Introduces a new boundary condition type 'Prescribed_displacement' that
reads nodal displacements from an external text file and applies them as
Dirichlet BCs on a wall face. Used for moving-boundary simulations where
the wall trajectory is prescribed from image registration.

Files modified:
- consts.h: new bType_prescribedDisp enum value and aliases
- Parameters.h/cpp: new 'Prescribed_displacement_file_path' XML parameter
- read_files.h/cpp: new read_prescribed_disp_txt() function; BC parsing
  in read_bc() dispatches to it when bc_type is 'Prescribed_displacement'
  or 'PrescribedDisp'. Excludes cap nodes shared with other faces.
- set_bc.cpp: new branch in set_bc_dir_l() for bType_prescribedDisp,
  delegating to igbc() for linear interpolation in time
- vtk_xml.cpp: writes the deformed mesh (reference coords + displacement)
  into VTU output when mvMsh is active, so ParaView shows the moving
  geometry directly without WarpByVector.
